<subSubSection id="58BCB1D6A523FFFEFF07FF5FFD4E721A" pageId="11" pageNumber="196" type="description">
<paragraph id="1019E25DA523FFFEFF07FF5FFD4E721A" blockId="11.[136,1452,230,1373]" pageId="11" pageNumber="196">
In our survey of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA523FFFEFECFFF5EFDF2713B" authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Greene" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[320,557,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="11" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA523FFFEFECFFF5EFDF2713B" box="[320,557,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="196">Cryptantha maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we discovered 
<specimenCount id="06A029D4A523FFFEFD6FFF5FFC59713B" box="[736,902,230,257]" pageId="11" pageNumber="196" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
that had been identified as that species but which had four, smooth nutlets, these slightly heteromorphic (
<figureCitation id="889DFED8A523FFFEFD79FEB2FCE4711E" box="[758,827,266,293]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="12.[136,229,1831,1853]" captionTargetBox="[245,1343,196,1806]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[237,1350,190,1807]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6. Cryptantha pondii. A. Close-up of single plant of presumed lectotype specimen (US41006), confirmed by Johnston (1928) as being correctly identified. Note linear, pustulate leaves and bracts at base of cymules. B,C. Images from Gentry 8684, 13 March 1949 (HCIB21969). B. Four nutlets removed from fruit, showing smooth surface and slight size heteromorphism. C. Close-up of cymules, showing linear bracts and relatively large corollas. D–F. Images from Philbrick B74-84, 25 March 1974 (SBBG49613). D. Fruit with four, smooth nutlets removed. Note finely hirsute calyx marginal region with ascending trichomes, as well as hispid calyx midrib of stouter trichomes. E. Close-up of four nutlets attached to gynobase. Note slight heteromorphism in size and slight extension of style tip/stigma from nutlet apices. F. Cymules, showing appressed-strigose vestiture of axes, scattered linear flower bracts, and relatively large corolla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426148" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426148/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="196">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). In discovering the publication of 
<bibRefCitation id="74379FACA523FFFEFB48FEB2FAA1711F" author="Johnston, I. M." box="[1223,1406,266,292]" pageId="11" pageNumber="196" pagination="73 - 83" refId="ref13085" refString="Johnston, I. M. (1928) Studies in the Boraginaceae - VII. 2. Notes on various Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 81: 73 - 83." type="journal article" year="1928">Johnston (1928)</bibRefCitation>
, we realized that this was the true 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA523FFFEFE59FE97FDE07173" authorityName=", Johnston" authorityYear="1928" box="[470,575,302,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="11" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pondii">
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA523FFFEFE59FE97FDE07173" box="[470,575,302,329]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="196">C. pondii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. To date, we are aware of only three collections of 
<emphasis id="22D23E4FA523FFFEFBF3FE97FB347173" box="[1148,1259,302,329]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="196">
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA523FFFEFBF3FE97FB387173" authorityName=", Johnston" authorityYear="1928" box="[1148,1255,302,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="11" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pondii">C. pondii</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
including that of the 
<typeStatus id="CF1D5CFFA523FFFEFF3DFEEBFF3A7156" box="[178,229,339,365]" pageId="11" pageNumber="196">type</typeStatus>
, all from 
<collectingRegion id="D2622CBFA523FFFEFEDEFEEAFDF17157" box="[337,558,338,364]" country="Mexico" name="Baja California Sur" pageId="11" pageNumber="196">Baja California Sur</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="68B1A2CDA523FFFEFDB6FEEAFD4D7157" box="[569,658,338,364]" name="Mexico" pageId="11" pageNumber="196">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. One collection has duplicates for a total of five herbarium specimens, but two collections consist of single known herbarium specimens (see below; recall that we were unable to locate the presumed “ 
<typeStatus id="CF1D5CFFA523FFFEFE88FE22FEE3718F" box="[263,316,410,436]" pageId="11" pageNumber="196">type</typeStatus>
” cited by Johnston, but did locate his cited “isotype,” treated here as a designated isolectotype). Two of the collections are from the extreme western portion of the 
<taxonomicName id="D7A699DEA523FFFEFCBEFE06FC4B71E3" box="[817,916,446,472]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vizcaino" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="11" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Vizcaíno</taxonomicName>
peninsula and one is from Natividad Island, just off the coast from that area (
<figureCitation id="889DFED8A523FFFEFE4FFE5AFDEC71C7" box="[448,563,482,508]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[136,229,950,972]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,194,919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[152,1436,190,926]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. A,B. Cryptantha pondii, distribution map of three known collections. Georeference point for the type, Pond 22, approximate; that of Gentry 8684 placed as a centroid of three different georeferenced estimates. Maps from ©Google 2020, INEGI Data." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426150" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426150/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="196">Fig. 7A,B</figureCitation>
). The three collections are listed here (georeferenced coordinates and elevations indicated with “*”, estimated from label data):
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
